column3: str
As ever, Mumukko seeks a pair of idle hands to carry out her bidding.
Speak with crew members wearing new equipment.
Speak with Mumukko.
I know I needn't ask, but have you some time on your hands, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>?
What will you say?
I know I needn't answer, but indeed I do!
Hm, then perhaps I needn't answer...
Then we have an unspoken understanding!
Oh, don't play coy! You do, don't you?
What will you say?
Okay, you win.
What if I truly didn't? Wouldn't you feel awful?
I always do.
Well played, but I won't be fooled. If you <Emphasis>truly</Emphasis> had better things to do, you wouldn't be standing here!
We've recently begun distributing two new types of equipment to contributors. Thus far, reception seems positive.
As they were costly to develop, however, I must determine whether this has been a worthwhile investment of time and resources.
All the more so given that I was the one who approved the proposal to begin with. 'Tis a poor manager who scrutinizes everything but her own judgment.
Thus, I should like you to survey the individuals making use of our cutting-edge gear. To ensure candid responses, you understand.
I'm sure you'll find no few fitting subjects right here at Terra Firma!
If you see anyone wearing a shiny new suit, kindly ask for their thoughts. There's no more to the assignment than that.
Why, my new powersuit is an absolute delight! In my opinion, strength augmentation is its most useful feature.
In this garb, even a bookworm bereft of biceps can lift heavy cargo with ease─and I daresay we Sharlayans could do with the help. Ha!
It has a diverse range of other functions, too─each implemented based on input from the entire crew.
I am certain other early adopters have found their suits a boon as well. How fortunate that the initiative chose to invest in them!
My opinion on the powersuit? I suppose the feedback stage <Emphasis>is</Emphasis> a vital part of development... Let me think.
Well, the helm's pretty great. Roomy enough for my ears to fit comfortably, and the filter supplies clean, breathable air in even the most toxic environments.
The best part, though? If your task calls for a lighter touch, you can wear it <Emphasis>without</Emphasis> the suit! If that's not innovation, I don't know what is!
I'll bet Mumukko sent you, didn't she? Well, you can tell her we all <Emphasis>love</Emphasis> the powersuit!
Fabulous! Hold that pose, please!
Pshhh... Shkohhh... 'Tis I, the Dark Vizier! Challenge me if you dare, my child, but know this: you underestimate the power of...<Emphasis>the Darkness.</Emphasis>
In this garb, I wield the power of the galaxy itself. Its magnificence is beyond question. Mwahahaha!
My helm is the crown of our Cosmic Empire! Through a veil of crimson, I see the force of the aether spilling from every last star!
Sorry, darling─he's rather immersed in his role at the moment. This attire attracts a subset of...passionate proponents, you see!
(He told me he likes to blow off steam after work by pretending he's an evil space overlord... Erm, is everything all right back on Etheirys...?)
Shkohhh...! The corruption of Oizys feeds my power!
The camera loves you, darling! Give me fierce!
I take it you found enough participants for a representative sample, then.
First, I'd like to hear the feedback you received from the powersuit users. Suggestions? Complaints?
What will you say?
The strength augmentation has been well received.
People are raving about the helm's versatility.
They fit well! Particularly around the ears.
Sounds like a worthy investment to me! I'll arrange for mass production at once.
And the star admiral attire? Is it too ostentatious?
What will you say?
Its glory fills the wearer with galactic power!
It inspires...enthusiasm, shall we say.
Pshhh... Shkohhh...
I...see? Well, if it improves morale, I'll allow it.
Don't tell me it's bewitched you, too... Rest assured I won't dare to cancel production, lest the enthusiasts come for me!
I'm told the costume originates from an opera with a dedicated following in Labyrinthos─an interstellar epic whose author is as yet unknown.
I was skeptical of its proposed value to the initiative, but it was so highly requested by ardent advocates that we had no choice but to concede.
Perhaps I ought to try it on myself, that I might better understand its appeal... One moment.
Mumukko!? What in Mother's name are ye wearin', lass!?
How to put this... You wear it so well, it makes me feel...unsettled? Afraid?
She's frightenin' enough in her usual getup! Take it off, I beg of ye!
Oh ho ho...
They may claim to have no time for Mumukko, but none dare defy the <Emphasis>Cosmic Executive</Emphasis>!
